summary: Another Detail in “Good Omens” I have seen many amazing posts about the subtle and perfect little details that the cast and crew...
body:
Another Detail in “Good Omens”

I have seen many amazing posts about the subtle and perfect little details that the cast and crew have put into this wonderful show, but today it occurred to me that there was this one small detail that I have yet not seen anyone mention before and which I think should be noted.

In the book, it is said about Crowley that he doesn’t blink much and, honestly, when I watched the show and whenever Crowley had his glasses off and it even seemed to me with his glasses on, he indeed did not blink. He squints occasionally but he does not blink. Correct me if I am wrong, of course! Still, I think this is yet another marvellous little thing that makes this show even more invaluable.

Bonus* : Full respect to David Tennant’s eyes which had to work a lot with contact lenses, sunglasses and not blinking. Oh, and fire! And often all together at the same time. Keep up the good work, David Tennant’s eyes!
